[04:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'images, you need to describe what each image actually is, so the model knows which one you\'re referring to in the text prompt. In my workflow, I\'m using prompt relay for the text prompting structure. In the global prompt, this is where I define each reference image.'

[04:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, for example, image two, long hair, black and purple clothing. That\'s my character. Short description, but enough for the model to understand which image I\'m talking about. Same'

[05:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'thing for the other character reference and the background image. All defined in the global prompt. Then, I move to the segment prompts. This is where you describe the character\'s actions and camera movements'

[05:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for each segment. So, that\'s the standard prompt relay structure I covered in a previous video. The negative prompt. This is interesting. Normally, when you use the Distill Laura or distilled'

[05:29] [scene:talk]
